##  Workbook Structure

This Excel workbook is organized into multiple worksheets, each serving a specific purpose in the data analysis process.

| Worksheet | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Clean Sales Data** | Cleaned and transformed dataset used for analysis. Removed inconsistencies, standardized data, and created calculated columns. |
| **Sales by Country** | Country-wise sales summary showing revenue distribution across different regions. |
| **Invoice Summary** | Invoice-level analysis including transaction totals and sales summaries. |
| **Questions** | Business questions defined before analysis to guide insights and dashboard creation. |
| **Pivot** | Pivot Tables used to summarize and analyze sales, customers, products, and other key metrics. |
| **KPIs** | Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) such as Total Sales, Orders, Customers, Average Order Value, and other business metrics. |
| **Insight Pivot** | Additional Pivot Tables created specifically to generate business insights and trends. |
| **Insights & Trends** | Final observations, business insights, and actionable recommendations derived from the analysis. |

